commit_message:
Fix unit tests in python3

Fix the check_output in unit tests, the result was being
intrepid as a byte string which caused unit tests to fail.
This patch makes it a utf-8 string.

Change-Id: Iba5c50762846ef5266eddd397aca44b01d411354
Signed-off-by: Chuck Short <chucks@redhat.com>

(2 comments)

This looks good to me but a couple of suggestions:

* put this before the API implementation (which I've just rebased to master to clear the merge conflict and to get rid of the references to the allocation schema but)
* add functional (non gabbi) tests in placement/db for the case it is fixing

Then in the API patch, fix the todo.

The order you have it in means that we would release a broken /reshaper."}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2018-07-24 13:38:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

(2 comments)

> add functional (non gabbi) tests in placement/db for the case it is fixing

This seemed wasteful/redundant given that the gabbi tests are covering it.

> The order you have it in means that we would release a broken /reshaper.

Yeah, but we're holding the series so we can merge it all at once.

I can switch them if you feel strongly about it, but it seems like a nontrivial amount of work for little gain."}, {'account_id': 11564, 'date': '2018-07-24 13:54:36.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: -Code-Review

(1 comment)

There is definitely a race condition for scenarios where a provider has no allocations or inventory specified in the reshaper request payload. See inline.

That said, the race condition is small and we'd need to refactor the handler code to pass in the resource provider object that was used to initially verify the supplied provider generation to the reshape() function.

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-07-23 21:03:15.000000000', 'message': "reshaper: Look up provider if not in inventories

Per the referenced bug, we weren't accounting for the scenario where a
reshape operation was removing *all* inventories for a provider (which
could be fairly common). With this fix, we do a three-stage lookup of
the provider object: If it's not in the inventories, we look in the
allocations; if it's not in the allocations, we look it up in the
database.

Change-Id: I594bb64f87c61b7ffd39c19e0fd42c4c087a3a11
Closes-Bug: #1783130

commit_message:
reshaper: Look up provider if not in inventories

Per the referenced bug, we weren't accounting for the scenario where a
reshape operation was removing *all* inventories for a provider (which
could be fairly common). With this fix, we do a three-stage lookup of
the provider object: If it's not in the inventories, we look in the
allocations; if it's not in the allocations, we look it up in the
database.

Change-Id: I594bb64f87c61b7ffd39c19e0fd42c4c087a3a11
Closes-Bug: #1783130

commit_message:
Prevent verify-config from IndexError

verify-config raises IndexError when tempest.conf
contains an empty api_extensions list.
The patch fixes that and adds a few unit tests to
that.

Change-Id: Ia9abea77e3baeb9418cb1869cec2a159cdc9fd48
Related-Bug: #1786915

commit_message:
Add trait query to placement perf check

This updates the EXPLANATION and sets the pinned version placeload
to the just release 0.3.0. This ought to hold us for a while. If
we need to do this again, we should probably switch to using
requirements files in some fashion, but I'm hoping we can avoid
that until later, potentially even after placement extraction
when we will have to moving and changing this anyway.

Change-Id: Ia3383c5dbbf8445254df774dc6ad23f2b9a3721e

commit_message:
Add explanatory prefix to post_test_perf output

The pirate on crack output of placeload can be confusing
so this change adds a prefix to the placement-perf.txt log
file so that it is somewhat more self-explanatory.

This change also pins the version of placeload because the
explanation is version dependent.

Change-Id: I055adb5f6004c93109b17db8313a7fef85538217

commit_message:
Blacklist pysaml2 4.6.0

Version 4.6.0 of pysaml2 is failing to install with python2 due to:

  https://github.com/IdentityPython/pysaml2/commit/9c7b0014ccc4229031813ddcc5f6790b59540df5

This commit blacklists that specific version so that we use 4.5.0
instead, which works until a new version is available. Once that
happens, we can bump the upper constraint and keep 4.6.0 on the
blacklist.

Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/597427
Change-Id: I5abf136d28fa82a4fe3abd642e20128279ae8090

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

commit_message:
[placement] Make _ensure_aggregate context not independent

The use of the independent context on _ensure_aggregate appears to
be unnecessary. It causes file-based uses of SQLite dbs to fail
(with database locked errors, as reported in the associated bug,
1789633) and thus may mask issues with other databases. Adding the
independent context manager was the result of a series of "throw
stuff at the wall and see what sticks" patches, but it looks now
that it is not required, and in some situations causes problems.

Runs through the gate show that the behavior it was fixing (as
described in bug 1786703) is not happening.

Change-Id: I1f325d55ec256db34a4c3bbd230dcd8a91bce542
Related-Bug: #1786703
Closes-Bug: #1789633

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: Ib90c91162d748f9b8aab2e3075a24c63e662da12

commit_message:
Add 1 sec sleep after delete in v3/test_tokens

failure:
  The assertRaises(NotFound, ...) call fails with[1]

work around / solution:
  I'm not sure how widely applicable this case is, I noticed we add
  a sleep call in some of our identitiy tests for synchronization
  of tokens[2]. So it seems acceptable to me to propose a 1 second
  sleep after this delete so that this test can pass sucessfully in
  our production environment.

[1] http://paste.openstack.org/show/728970/
[2] http://codesearch.openstack.org/?q=sleep&i=nope&files=identity&repos=tempest

Change-Id: I52aab01108c4404244198f31a01ba49917acae80

[{'created': '2018-08-22 17:27:41.000000000', 'message': 'Add Django-debreach to global-requirements.txt

This provides Basic/extra mitigation against the BREACH attack for
Django projects.

More details- https://github.com/lpomfrey/django-debreach

The blueprint has been approved to add this-
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/horizon/+spec/mitigate-breach-attacks

It is being targetted for stein.

Is the library actively maintained?

Last release Dec 21, 2017 and no indications of project being abandoned.

Is the library good code?

We at AT&T have been using this code from quite sometime and have faced
no issues.

Is the library license compatible?

Yes.

Is the library already packaged in the distros we target (Ubuntu latest / Fedora latest)?

Yes.

Is the function of this library already covered by other libraries in global-requirements.txt?

No.

Is the library required for OpenStack project or related dev or infrastructure setup? (Answer to this should be Yes, of course) Which?

Yes, this is needed for Projects based on Django.

If the library release is managed by the Openstack release process does it use the cycle-with-intermediary release type?

No.

Change-Id: I32f11e089fc794444ef267b463c7fb2ad8cfa96a

commit_message:
Add Django-debreach to global-requirements.txt

This provides Basic/extra mitigation against the BREACH attack for
Django projects.

More details- https://github.com/lpomfrey/django-debreach

The blueprint has been approved to add this-
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/horizon/+spec/mitigate-breach-attacks

It is being targetted for stein.

Is the library actively maintained?

Last release Dec 21, 2017 and no indications of project being abandoned.

Is the library good code?

We at AT&T have been using this code from quite sometime and have faced
no issues.

Is the library license compatible?

Yes.

Is the library already packaged in the distros we target (Ubuntu latest / Fedora latest)?

Yes.

Is the function of this library already covered by other libraries in global-requirements.txt?

No.

Is the library required for OpenStack project or related dev or infrastructure setup? (Answer to this should be Yes, of course) Which?

Yes, this is needed for Projects based on Django.

If the library release is managed by the Openstack release process does it use the cycle-with-intermediary release type?

No.

Change-Id: I32f11e089fc794444ef267b463c7fb2ad8cfa96a

commit_message:
Remove a few extensions from NETWORK_API_EXTENSIONS

This commit removes the following extensions from the list.
	timestamp_core
	tag
	tag_ext

Those extensions have been removed long before. [1] [2]
The mismatch has been exposed by the recently added
tempest test case. [3]

[1] I2ee2ed4c713d88345adc55b022feb95653eec663
[2] I97095453610fff114d999a526d67e78119546ff5
[3] I4c59f407c30020e3865e96e67a1b61361e699014

Also, make the grenade job non-voting for now because
it would take long to fix it.
1. It needs to be fixed in the base branch (right now
   it's stable/queens) as grenade uses the base branch's
   tempest.conf (thus NETWORK_API_EXTENSIONS) as it is
   for the target branch.
2. Right now stable/queens gate is broken for unrelated reasons

Closes-Bug: #1789323
Change-Id: Ib865c5b406097c5196d8a95cfefc6e5513c1e40d

commit_message:
Lower hostnames in ssh_known_hosts

Due to [1] ansible always access servers lowcase. This patch fixes generatation
of ssh_known_hosts in order to access servers properly when uppercase is
present in hostname

[1] https://github.com/ansible/ansible/pull/26850/commits/aa4278e5f3ac2fc70c18ebd2f135378fa76776c7

Change-Id: Ib25832496d6504def436414b9c2903cbfe5854d4
Resolves: rhbz#1619556

commit_message:
Add option block to ensure apache2 is enabled correctly

The apache2 monitoring process requires a couple interactions to deploy
successfully. This change will ensure that if the apache2 monitoring
fails, in any way, it does not block the deployment.

Change-Id: Ibe35197a1c65f4abe9e4870c07ee15f37f9a58ab
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

not always populated within a container. This change converts the UUID

commit_message:
Add device monitoring in containers

The existing device monitoring was relying on block UUIDs which are
not always populated within a container. This change converts the UUID
use to device path which is always available no matter container engine
type.

Change-Id: Iec1493a58d9aab8b2a9cb67b9202e1751606bbc4
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Tempest: add option to execute cleanup always

This PS makes to control cleanup action.
If there are FAILED cases, temepest-test returns non-zero code.
_run-tests.sh.tpl exit immediately without cleanup.
if set Values.conf.cleanup.force to true, cleanup is excuted always.

Change-Id: Ie2ffee8faa9561f8acb4dc762fcfa9a282477f50
Closes-Bug: #1788076

commit_message:
Update metering driver to load interface driver

Currently the metering iptables driver is using the old method
to load the interface driver. This patch allows it to load
interface driver via stevedore aliases.

Change-Id: I9e3027c1ec695ec3a09db0c53a0388e406e4ced6
Related-Bug: #1504536
(cherry picked from commit 38309ca4dc79e033a7b8384f4e9f1224c5a69524)

remove documentation job from in-tree config

configure it in project-config and not here.

the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some

normalized.

commit_message:
Reduce qos rpc times on the ovs-agent side

When multiple ports are bound to qos-policy with the same id,
ovs-agent should check whether the cache has policy information
instead of directly reading rpc when processing the port.

Change-Id: I88f9f5af95439f1536799169390764c89109f467
Closes-Bug: #1783559

[{'created': '2017-11-01 20:15:57.000000000', 'message': "Don't log exception trace with ComputeHostNotFound warnings on startup

When we're logging a warning within a ComputeHostNotFound exception
block, oslo.log appears to be automatically logging the exception
trace. When starting a nova-compute service for the first time, these
ComputeHostNotFound warnings are expected until the ResourceTracker
creates the ComputeNode records in the cell database, so tracing the
warning is ugly and clutters up the log on the first startup.

Passing exc_info=False should tell the log handler to not trace the
exception that's in scope.

Change-Id: I95db59f9f5a72794e88f4f234bb19d357496a75b
"}]
commit_message:
Don't log exception trace with ComputeHostNotFound warnings on startup

When we're logging a warning within a ComputeHostNotFound exception
block, oslo.log appears to be automatically logging the exception
trace. When starting a nova-compute service for the first time, these
ComputeHostNotFound warnings are expected until the ResourceTracker
creates the ComputeNode records in the cell database, so tracing the
warning is ugly and clutters up the log on the first startup.

Passing exc_info=False should tell the log handler to not trace the
exception that's in scope.

Change-Id: I95db59f9f5a72794e88f4f234bb19d357496a75b

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-05-16 20:21:07.000000000', 'message': "WIP: Don't count volume over quota when disabling compute

When booting from volume, nova doesn't check volume quota
before we actually try to create the volumes during
_prep_block_device. If the project is at their volume quota
limit, Cinder will fail and we'll get an OverQuota exception
during _build_resources. This is also counted as a build
failure in _failed_build() which checks the
[compute]/consecutive_build_service_disable_threshold config
option and can eventually auto-disable the nova-compute service
on this host, e.g. if Dastardly Dan is already over quota for
volumes but continually makes lots of consecutive build
requests for new servers, they could eventually disable the
compute services in the cloud.

This handles the specific volume OverQuota case and raises a
new type of exception, BuildAbortExceptionDoNotDisable,
which is eventually handled in _do_build_and_run_instance and
returns a new type of build_results enum which
build_and_run_instance can use to determine if it should be
counted against a systemic consecutive build failure or just
consider it as user-error and reset the build failure counter.

Change-Id: Ic27a361364a84bad259d9075085b4b28b5516a34
Partial-Bug: #1742102
"}]
commit_message:
WIP: Don't count volume over quota when disabling compute

When booting from volume, nova doesn't check volume quota
before we actually try to create the volumes during
_prep_block_device. If the project is at their volume quota
limit, Cinder will fail and we'll get an OverQuota exception
during _build_resources. This is also counted as a build
failure in _failed_build() which checks the
[compute]/consecutive_build_service_disable_threshold config
option and can eventually auto-disable the nova-compute service
on this host, e.g. if Dastardly Dan is already over quota for
volumes but continually makes lots of consecutive build
requests for new servers, they could eventually disable the
compute services in the cloud.

This handles the specific volume OverQuota case and raises a
new type of exception, BuildAbortExceptionDoNotDisable,
which is eventually handled in _do_build_and_run_instance and
returns a new type of build_results enum which
build_and_run_instance can use to determine if it should be
counted against a systemic consecutive build failure or just
consider it as user-error and reset the build failure counter.

Change-Id: Ic27a361364a84bad259d9075085b4b28b5516a34
Partial-Bug: #1742102

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I8ab3b15a4a2dae363b760987ab36b71fa11f2789
Story: #2002586
Task: #24341

messages: [{'account_id': 26297, 'date': '2018-08-15 06:52:29.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 17499, 'date': '2018-08-15 09:03:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 3153, 'date': '2018-08-15 15:40:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 14985, 'date': '2018-08-29 20:38:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-15 06:52:29.000000000', 'message': 'fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I40c03aecc8984f20f9bffdb1bebff14b594fae73
'}]
commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I40c03aecc8984f20f9bffdb1bebff14b594fae73

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-29 04:43:17.000000000', 'message': "Infra repo retirement - step 1

This is step 1 in retiring some infra repositories. It adds noop-jobs to
repos that we want to retire for those that have jobs.

Repos to retire are:
openstack-infra/activity-board
openstack-infra/beaker-localhost
openstack-infra/beaker-nodepool
openstack-infra/err2d2
openstack-infra/js-afs-blob-store
openstack-infra/js-openstack-registry-hooks
openstack-infra/js-generator-openstack
openstack-infra/pypi-mirror
openstack-infra/trystack-site
openstack-infra/puppet-vinz
openstack-infra/vinz
openstack-infra/vinz-webclient

Rationale:

openstack-infra/activity-board:
  Was part of bitergia work with openstack which is no longer done

openstack-infra/beaker-localhost
openstack-infra/beaker-nodepool
  These may have been attempts at having puppet beaker testing
  play nice with our CI but we hacked around it by pointing the
  beaker config at localhost. There are no commits here should be
  safe to retire.

openstack-infra/err2d2
  Part of a plan to make our IRC bots errbot driven but more
  recent spec has us sticking with supybot fork and plugins.

openstack-infra/js-afs-blob-store
openstack-infra/js-openstack-registry-hooks
  Allowed us to mirror npm packages on afs until npm grew too
  large. I think we can retire this as we don't mirror npm any
  longer.

openstack-infra/js-generator-openstack
  Appears to be a cookiecutter like system for openstack js
  projects. Maybe we should just use cookiecutter?

openstack-infra/pypi-mirror
  Was tooling to make a mirror of a subset of pypi. We moved to
  bandersnatch and now just proxy cache pypi.

openstack-infra/trystack-site
  Trystack has been retired due to spam and the passport program
  is suggested instead.

openstack-infra/puppet-vinz
openstack-infra/vinz
openstack-infra/vinz-webclient
  Project to provide alternate Gerrit UI that never got commits.

Change-Id: If91073b58e2feee3de26558508f88067a7132331

commit_message:
Infra repo retirement of 18 repos - step 1

This is step 1 in retiring some infra repositories. It adds noop-jobs to
repos that we want to retire for those that have jobs.

Repos to retire are:
openstack-infra/activity-board
openstack-infra/beaker-localhost
openstack-infra/beaker-nodepool
openstack-infra/err2d2
openstack-infra/featuretracker
openstack-infra/js-afs-blob-store
openstack-infra/js-openstack-registry-hooks
openstack-infra/js-generator-openstack
openstack-infra/puppet-docker_registry
openstack-infra/puppet-featuretracker
openstack-infra/puppet-releasestatus
openstack-infra/pypi-mirror
openstack-infra/releasestatus
openstack-infra/trystack-site
openstack-infra/puppet-vinz
openstack-infra/vinz
openstack-infra/vinz-webclient
openstack-infra/zuul-packaging

Rationale:

openstack-infra/activity-board:
  Was part of bitergia work with openstack which is no longer done

openstack-infra/beaker-localhost
openstack-infra/beaker-nodepool
  These may have been attempts at having puppet beaker testing
  play nice with our CI but we hacked around it by pointing the
  beaker config at localhost. There are no commits here should be
  safe to retire.

openstack-infra/featuretracker
openstack-infra/puppet-featuretracker
  The product WG is abandoned, see
  http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/user-committee/2018-February/002599.html.
  The website  http://featuretracker.openstack.org is also dead.

openstack-infra/err2d2
  Part of a plan to make our IRC bots errbot driven but more
  recent spec has us sticking with supybot fork and plugins.

openstack-infra/js-afs-blob-store
openstack-infra/js-openstack-registry-hooks
  Allowed us to mirror npm packages on afs until npm grew too
  large. I think we can retire this as we don't mirror npm any
  longer.

openstack-infra/js-generator-openstack
  Appears to be a cookiecutter like system for openstack js
  projects. Maybe we should just use cookiecutter?

openstack-infra/pypi-mirror
  Was tooling to make a mirror of a subset of pypi. We moved to
  bandersnatch and now just proxy cache pypi.

openstack-infra/trystack-site
  Trystack has been retired due to spam and the passport program
  is suggested instead.

openstack-infra/puppet-docker_registry
  This is unused, there are other alternatives that can be used.

openstack-infra/puppet-vinz
openstack-infra/vinz
openstack-infra/vinz-webclient
  Project to provide alternate Gerrit UI that never got commits.

openstack-infra/releasestatus
openstack-infra/puppet-releasestatus
  releasestatus is not used since December 2015, see
  https://review.openstack.org/#/c/254817

openstack-infra/zuul-packaging
  This is unused and outdated.

Mail sent out:
  http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-August/133958.html

commit_message:
DNM: Use Queens UCA

This updates the UCA usage from Pike to Queens. As a result,
the various volume multiattach checks can also be removed
because the Queens UCA has libvirt 4.0.0.

Change-Id: Icb971831c8d4fe5f940d9e7993d53f1c3765e30f

determine that, so just don't move it at all.

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I4e415392950f00a238de58ff2f99ac05493f54a0
Story: #2002586
Task: #24341

commit_message:
Fix Non-ASCII decode failure in heat chef-hook

Any non-ASCII character appeart in the chef command output will cause
json.dump to throw UnicodeDecodeError. This will cause deployment
failure though it was successful.

Change-Id: I79d6e0c3d4ad5ea77e31ff3295cce2a8c5f2d4bf
Closes-Bug: #1709026

commit_message:
Helm-Toolkit: TLS cert generator

This PS adds a function to generate tls certificates from a
CA. It also adds a script to generate a snakeoil ca for dev
and future gating work.

Change-Id: Ic94a9ab5fa3ebb912b507008a6b2f78e16dade67
Signed-off-by: Pete Birley <pete@port.direct>

Ok I think I may see where the problem is - in overcloud-prep-containers.sh as generated by quickstart, we see:

  PREPARE_ARGS=${PREPARE_ARGS:-"-e /usr/share/openstack-tripleo-heat-templates/environments/docker.yaml"}

This worked fine when the environments/docker.yaml file referred to all-the-container things, but since containers are now the default I guess we need that to reference the base environment instead?'}, {'account_id': 4328, 'date': '2018-08-21 15:34:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

To clarify, I changed the default to look like:

  PREPARE_ARGS=${PREPARE_ARGS:-"-e /usr/share/openstack-tripleo-heat-templates/overcloud-resource-registry-puppet.yaml"}

This then downloads all the images, which probably indicates we're not passing a specific PREPARE_ARGS in CI (which could potentially save some time?) but it gets past the issue for me locally.'}, {'account_id': 12715, 'date': '2018-08-21 18:09:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)

The scenario009 job is broken without this, so I think we should merge it unless we have another solution ready to go.

It seems like we may have to add support for using a j2 template environment to the container image prepare command.'}, {'account_id': 12715, 'date': '2018-08-21 18:10:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

ci looks like this:

http://logs.openstack.org/95/582495/13/check/tripleo-ci-centos-7-scenario009-multinode-oooq/eb9e67a/logs/undercloud/home/zuul/containers-default-parameters.yaml.txt.gz'}, {'account_id': 12715, 'date': '2018-08-21 18:22:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

trying with https://review.openstack.org/594504 to see if we get only the containers we need. If that works we can abandon this.'}, {'account_id': 4328, 'date': '2018-08-22 07:47:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

> To clarify, I changed the default to look like:
 > 
 > PREPARE_ARGS=${PREPARE_ARGS:-"-e /usr/share/openstack-tripleo-heat-templates/overcloud-resource-registry-puppet.yaml"}
 > 
 > This then downloads all the images, which probably indicates we're
 > not passing a specific PREPARE_ARGS in CI (which could potentially
 > save some time?) but it gets past the issue for me locally.

Yeah, we should pass a roles file to the prepare command to limit the container images to the ones that are going to be used in the deployment.'}, {'account_id': 13039, 'date': '2018-08-23 10:48:14.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

I'm trying to think of a reason why the keepalived services was not added to environments/docker.yaml in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/536071/ but can't see one. At some point, we should probably consider deleting environments/docker.yaml if it doesn't diverge from the defaults anymore."}, {'account_id': 6926, 'date': '2018-08-23 12:48:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Martin, IIUC
> Yeah, we should pass a roles file to the prepare command to limit the container images to the ones that are going to be used in the deployment.

we need some fixes to always specify the wanted role file for all of the supported deployment jobs?..'}, {'account_id': 12715, 'date': '2018-08-23 15:12:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

I have tried a few different things to solve this issue, and I have come back to thinking this is the best one.

We can not use the j2 template we use in deploy because we have different code for the container image prepare than we do for deploy. For container image prepare we silently ignore any -e files that do not actually exist on the filesystem[1]. Whereas for deploy we get the files from swift (where the j2 template is already stored and resolved)[2]

I also considered putting this in the scenario file itself... but we would then need to add it to the other scenarios that use keepalived (007 and 008) as they are also broken.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/python-tripleoclient/blob/master/tripleoclient/utils.py#L1199-L1200
[2] https://github.com/openstack/python-tripleoclient/blob/master/tripleoclient/v1/overcloud_deploy.py#L202-L204'}, {'account_id': 13039, 'date': '2018-08-23 15:15:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 13039, 'date': '2018-08-27 16:46:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Fix IPv6 for Cinder NetApp ONTAP drivers

NetApp ONTAP driver currently have some issues with IPv6:
 - The URL is not properly formatted when using in management path
 - NFS driver breaks when handling IPv6 addresses
 - iSCSI driver creates a URL that is not properly formatted when
 using IPv6 addresses

This patch fixes all issues related to IPv6 on NetApp ONTAP drivers.

Closes-bug: 1788419
Closes-bug: 1788460
Change-Id: I6eeca47997c7134d6604874bea48eab7cab6c1a2

commit_message:
Monasca driver poll time type fixed

When custom poll time is specified in CLI monasca
datasource instantiation, a string type is used,
causing eventlet errors.

The needed conversion to int is added in this patch.

Change-Id: I5f4873752f41f7d0a4b0903f1f9e4d41eb05e810
Closes-Bug: 1762586
(cherry picked from commit eabd6883665cb65d1fc612aef6e7e1071c2c23f1)

commit_message:
Detection of errors for Dell PowerConnect devices

Adds some commonly seen error messages in Dell PowerConnect switches:

% Incomplete command
VLAN was not created by user
Configuration Database locked by another application - try later

If these messages are found in the response from a device, an exception
will be raised.

Change-Id: Ia2d27cd659611cd7dad6663f1ac90c457658f697
Story: 2003148
Task: 24643

messages:
[{'account_id': 14826, 'date': '2018-08-15 11:33:25.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 24828, 'date': '2018-08-18 06:24:27.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

LGTM, I think decorate the send_commands_to_device would be simpler, unless you'll do more checks based on specific interface instead of switch command.

Considering error message is device specific, I suppose it make sense if we just provide checking mechanism at base interface, and move actual checks down to drivers underneath, wdyt?"}, {'account_id': 14826, 'date': '2018-08-20 08:24:29.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

> LGTM, I think decorate the send_commands_to_device would be
 > simpler, unless you'll do more checks based on specific interface
 > instead of switch command.

I went with this approach so that we could pass in the operation as a parameter, in case a device wants to make the error checking more context-specific. It's only a few extra lines of code, so it seemed like a reasonable tradeoff.

 > Considering error message is device specific, I suppose it make
 > sense if we just provide checking mechanism at base interface, and
 > move actual checks down to drivers underneath, wdyt?

The error messages are device-specific, see https://review.openstack.org/#/c/589961/2 for an example of adding messages. A device could provide a different checking implementation by overriding check_output().

The next patch, https://review.openstack.org/#/c/592010/1, makes the error detection more flexible by making each supported error an object. This would allow a device to provide different types of error checking than regex, and to encode more information into the error, such as whether it is temporary or fatal.

Does that answer your question?"}, {'account_id': 10239, 'date': '2018-08-21 16:48:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

(2 comments)'}, {'account_id': 14826, 'date': '2018-08-21 17:22:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow-1'}, {'account_id': 14826, 'date': '2018-08-21 17:23:49.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 10239, 'date': '2018-08-22 07:53:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 24828, 'date': '2018-08-23 03:27:39.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

I was considering error checking for specific command instead of interface, it's ok now, I think that's not necessary."}, {'account_id': 14826, 'date': '2018-08-23 07:57:15.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

> I was considering error checking for specific command instead of
 > interface, it's ok now, I think that's not necessary.

That's something we could do with the changes in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/592010/1, by adding the relevant operations (port plug, add network etc.) to the ErrorDetector object."}, {'account_id': 12356, 'date': '2018-08-29 16:03:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1

(1 comment)'}]

commit_message:
Correct default number of threads

The default number of threads does not match the default
tested upstream[1], which can return errors for users when
requests begin backing up in the webserver due to a lack
of resources and the nature of the ironic API having some
synchronous requests.

Upstream ironic, as of the Rocky cycle, executed with uwsgi
which is configured for the same process count algorithm,
but enable threds. There does not appear to be an upper bound
to that setting, but accoriding to mod_wsgi documentation[3],
the default is 15 threads. The example shipped with ironic[4]
defaults to 10, which also seems to be a valid configuration.

[1]: https://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/ironic/tree/devstack/lib/ironic?h=stable/rocky#n1129
[2]: http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-dev/devstack/tree/lib/apache#n267
[3]: https://modwsgi.readthedocs.io/en/develop/configuration-directives/WSGIDaemonProcess.html
[4]: https://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/ironic/tree/etc/apache2/ironic?h=stable/rocky#n21

Story: #2003464
Task: #24724
rhbz: #1613995

Change-Id: I327219f96cfc0a69643ab6369cb8e831251f799c
(cherry picked from commit 037cd2cb5d332ba178d78390a3f5bcd75ce1e9e3)

commit_message:
Correct default number of threads

The default number of threads does not match the default
tested upstream[1], which can return errors for users when
requests begin backing up in the webserver due to a lack
of resources and the nature of the ironic API having some
synchronous requests.

Upstream ironic, as of the Rocky cycle, executed with uwsgi
which is configured for the same process count algorithm,
but enable threds. There does not appear to be an upper bound
to that setting, but accoriding to mod_wsgi documentation[3],
the default is 15 threads. The example shipped with ironic[4]
defaults to 10, which also seems to be a valid configuration.

[1]: https://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/ironic/tree/devstack/lib/ironic?h=stable/rocky#n1129
[2]: http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-dev/devstack/tree/lib/apache#n267
[3]: https://modwsgi.readthedocs.io/en/develop/configuration-directives/WSGIDaemonProcess.html
[4]: https://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/ironic/tree/etc/apache2/ironic?h=stable/rocky#n21

Task: #24724
rhbz: #1613995

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I531cb4ed277992c945e5710ac9bebc65af42045e
Story: #2002586
Task: #24292

commit_message:
ensure unique ironic node ID with UCS driver

The UCS driver info handling is split off the common
PrefixedDriverInfo implementation for the purpose of
generating unique node IDs in a driver-specific and
clean way.

This change un-deprecates `pm_service_profile` option
support.

Conflicts: tripleo_common/utils/nodes.py

Closes-Bug: #1739024
Change-Id: Ibabe216d3e2b1ea33adc1feaae7095e76cfad19d
(cherry picked from commit ea50e58eb6c4d0aab9d79a531a3644fd136993c5)

commit_message:
Remove deprecated Disco driver config opts

Some of the general config options were renamed in the
Pike release with disco driver specific config options.
This patch removes the deprecated names from these config
options.

[{'created': '2018-07-20 21:58:42.000000000', 'message': "Maintenance: Fix router ports

Prior to this patch the maintenance thread would fail to fix a router
port resource upon a failure in OVN to create it.

The maintence thread was calling the add_router_interface() method from
the l3_ovn.py module but, if the router port already existed in Neutron
(but didn't exist in OVN) that method would fail with a PortInUse
exception.

This patch accounts for that problem and if the port router already
exist in Neutron it will only fetch it from the database and continue
the work until it's created in the OVN database as well.

A new functional test has been added which to test this scenario.

There was no functional tests for the maintenance in the stable/queens
branch, so this patch is adding it.

Closes-Bug: #1746979
Change-Id: Iae500d17d0efe17f3460dc2f09356675d406abed

commit_message:
Maintenance: Fix router ports

Prior to this patch the maintenance thread would fail to fix a router
port resource upon a failure in OVN to create it.

The maintence thread was calling the add_router_interface() method from
the l3_ovn.py module but, if the router port already existed in Neutron
(but didn't exist in OVN) that method would fail with a PortInUse
exception.

This patch accounts for that problem and if the port router already
exist in Neutron it will only fetch it from the database and continue
the work until it's created in the OVN database as well.

A new functional test has been added which to test this scenario.

Backport note: This is squashing also f69b68d7d36c79bba211648acd5939ee3e52cd7a
which adds the functional tests to the maintenance feature.

Closes-Bug: #1746979
Change-Id: Iae500d17d0efe17f3460dc2f09356675d406abed

commit_message:
Skip L3 ha functional IPv6 test if IPv6 is disabled

Test test_ha_router_namespace_has_ipv6_forwarding_disabled requires
IPv6 to be enabled on host on which tests are run.
It is now skipped if IPv6 is disabled.

TrivialFix

Change-Id: Idaa93bf112b2d29a56e3e4a2535c7d3fa0c49db4

[{'created': '2018-08-28 06:53:11.000000000', 'message': "Fix neutron-openvswitch-agent Windows support

Currently, the neutron-openvswitch-agent does not start on Windows
due to Linux specific imports. This patch addresses this issue.

Also, we're wrapping the object returned by subprocess.Popen using
tpool.Proxy in order to prevent IO operations on the stream
handles from blocking other threads. Currently, the ovs db monitor
blocks the whole process.

Closes-Bug: #1775382

Co-Authored-By: Lucian Petrut <lpetrut@cloudbasesolutions.com>
Change-Id: I8bbc9d1f8332e5644a6071f599a7c6a66bef7928
(cherry picked from commit fee630efaa74ce3d193999944e5b3a331fb2fbd9)
"}]
commit_message:
Fix neutron-openvswitch-agent Windows support

Currently, the neutron-openvswitch-agent does not start on Windows
due to Linux specific imports. This patch addresses this issue.

Also, we're wrapping the object returned by subprocess.Popen using
tpool.Proxy in order to prevent IO operations on the stream
handles from blocking other threads. Currently, the ovs db monitor
blocks the whole process.

Closes-Bug: #1775382

Co-Authored-By: Lucian Petrut <lpetrut@cloudbasesolutions.com>
Change-Id: I8bbc9d1f8332e5644a6071f599a7c6a66bef7928
(cherry picked from commit fee630efaa74ce3d193999944e5b3a331fb2fbd9)

commit_message:
Add usage examples for standalone

Recently folks have been asking how to launch the VMs in the standalone
and be able to access them. The following patch provides examples on how
to consume the standalone resources and leverage tenant and provider
networks for the VMs and how to use only provider networks for the VMs.

Change-Id: I32b51374376db92ee6854fa7816b59bf12f97fc6

commit_message:
Random names for functional tests

In case of parallel execution random failures can happen due to name
collision.
The tempest-lib uses random names. One alternative is to add tempest-lib
as test dependency to osc-plugin and use
tempest.lib.common.utils.data_utils.rand_name, the other is to use
random generated names in all cases.

Change-Id: Ie066edba812adbea068f0eac88e939ad83ccfef3

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I0526b3d47519e5cca9ce491fe1220d9df13effc5
Story: #2002586
Task: #24292

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

commit_message:
Fix pep8 errors, pip 10 compatibility and devstack

This commit is a squash of backported fixes.

1) Recent pep8 upgrade and corresponding pycodestyle update break pep8 job
due to the new rules. This commit fixes the following new errors:

  - E711 comparison to None should be 'if cond is None:'
  - E402 module level import not at top of file
  - W503 line break before binary operator

2) pip 10 now reports an error when calling pip without package name,
effectively breaking stable branches. This patch also fix this by
modifying tox_install.sh

3) devstack: teach how to handle latest ODL release

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/584872/

Note(elod.illes): from the above commit the following parts were used:
- Pin rally to 0.12.1
- Use latest ODL version for jobs

Change-Id: I59b6682e6295ab77efc25c275b8a2b70923433db
(cherry picked from commit d899160a9161c1d3ccdeab66b7d1ec661a654bcd)
(cherry picked from commit 59075b8243e869774e29bd3b378723947c0b3a20)

VMAX Manila doc - including network setup steps

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I9b08dd8b6c0953c6e0a210279cfc30586e7030c5
Story: #2002586
Task: #24328

commit_message:
adapt configure_for_func_testing for stadium projects

Neutron Stadium projects may need the functional or fullstack setup
of Neutron's.

For this purpose this change modifies configure_for_func_testing so
that it still points to the right locations for fullstack test commands,
including when run from a venv that is not
created from neutron's repo but from another repo, typically a
neutron stadium project.

Needed-By: Ib2a4f1f258d39dcba370fe37799c56ad0e5ca8fd
Change-Id: I092ac244d67e31a2ca60c4bb83a88d477ef07b97

commit_message:
Remove the deprecated ZeroMQ driver

Users of the oslo.messaging RPC communications service must use
the rabbit ("rabbit://...") or AMQP 1.0 ("amqp://...") drivers.

Change-Id: If3474142f1fe99d41d7b4466061ed0e23ca38549
Closes-Bug: 1789259

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I6775392b45c36baf896f31d78c15c347111fe5b8
Story: #2002586

commit_message:
Switch inspection store to use stable docker image

The latest image is currently failing to download, with the following
error:

no matching manifest for unknown in the manifest list entries

This is currently blocking CI.

Change-Id: I3b4acadd53fe171e71ee16e0eb0b7a711fa97a4f

That makes perfect sense, and requires no extra API calls. Thanks Florian!'}, {'account_id': 9317, 'date': '2018-06-12 14:22:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 17888, 'date': '2018-06-13 15:06:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 10112, 'date': '2018-06-18 12:58:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 14985, 'date': '2018-06-19 22:04:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 9317, 'date': '2018-06-20 07:56:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

I'm not sure why it would be backwards incompatible, as none of the API interfaces are changing. Listing, loading, and running validations still works exactly the same from the workflow caller's perspective. The only difference is that we're now storing the validations in Swift. Note also that the validations that get installed to the local disk with the tripleo-validations package are still going to be on disk; we never remove them from there, only copy them to a Swift container."}, {'account_id': 14985, 'date': '2018-06-20 12:17:17.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

The backwards incompatibility is the ability to execute them off of disk. That's gone. As I mentioned, there may be cases where there is no swift/mistral which would work fine today but with this change will no longer work. I was asking that we not remove that bit of functionality so we can still tell the execution to run from disk."}, {'account_id': 9317, 'date': '2018-06-22 10:24:11.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

We're using Mistral as an engine to run validations. So if Mistral was gone we wouldn't be able to run validations at all. (Except if you used ansible-playbook to run them, but as I said, we're not removing validation yaml files from disk, so you can still do that after this change.)

Can you elaborate on what would be the situation in which Mistral/Swift would not be available. We are relying on these services in many places in TripleO (e.g. we're storing the deployment plan in Swift) so I think many things would stop working if we didn't have Swift and/or Mistral."}, {'account_id': 14985, 'date': '2018-06-22 14:16:15.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

So mistral/swift is only available if an undercloud is there. We're working on an all-in-one (containerized undercloud is based on this) which won't have mistral/swift available at the start.  The all-in-one cloud deploy won't have an external mistral/swift available at all. It would beneficial to still be able to execute the basic validation action manually (via ansible or otherwise) from disk w/o out mistral.  Validations themselves likely need to be executable before any actions are performed (ie. pre-undercloud validation) so requiring mistral/swift is not ideal in this case."}, {'account_id': 9317, 'date': '2018-06-24 09:33:00.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

Thanks for the clarification. In the situation you described, one would still be able to execute validations from the disk (we don't remove them from there) using Ansible directly (so no Mistral required). So this change doesn't introduce any dependency in that context."}, {'account_id': 14985, 'date': '2018-06-25 16:33:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: -Code-Review

I'll remove my -1. I guess my preference is to not remove the local validation processing utility functions and only adapt them to support the swift loading."}, {'account_id': 9317, 'date': '2018-07-02 11:28:05.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 9317, 'date': '2018-07-02 14:52:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

The container is supposed to be create in undercloud post install (https://github.com/openstack/tripleo-heat-templates/blob/master/extraconfig/post_deploy/undercloud_post.sh#L139-L145) but looks like it's not getting created: http://logs.openstack.org/13/569513/6/check/tripleo-ci-centos-7-containers-multinode/383f809/logs/undercloud/home/zuul/undercloud_install.log.txt.gz

commit_message:
Add support for custom validations

This patch introduces support for running custom validations by changing
the behavior of the validations actions ListValidationsAction,
ListGroupsAction and RunValidationAction.

Until now, these actions sourced validations from a directory on disk.
Now, these action are sourcing validations from the plan container
subdirectory (custom validations), or, if this is not available, from
the Swift container holding the default validations.

Change-Id: I9e9131b355312c53f12d154976d5d9cd706cc338
Implements: blueprint custom-validations
Depends-On: I338e139fa770ebb7bdcc1c0afb79eec062fada8b

commit_message:
Mention (unused) RP generation in POST /allocs/{c}

The schema accepts the (resource provider) 'generation' key in the
resource provider section of the allocations dictionary in the POST
/allocations/{consumer_uuid} request payload. As with PUT
/allocations/{consumer_uuid}, it is ignored. This was missing from the
API reference.

Change-Id: I2586875a60aba7a566f6c1b61ded133b8749031c

commit_message:
Correct handling of known configs in cfgvalidator datasource

cfgvalidator datasource did not update the set of known configs. Each
time config hashes were retrieved, the config was analyzed although it
was already registered. This bugfix simplifies the data structures used
and corrects the logic of the update process.

Change-Id: Ibc6098c815d2a21565f845f2d5af63bb1333f1a2
Closes-Bug: 1762330
(cherry picked from commit 2e97a2869ff818c0bb3d960e89a0d24dbf6244db)

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: Icfc7c6d0c887ecf7fbdc0d70c1ed136788b88475
Story: #2002586
Task: #24312

commit_message:
Avoid tox_install.sh for constraints support

We do not need tox_install.sh, pip can handle constraints itself
and install the project correctly. Thus update tox.ini and remove
the now obsolete tools/tox_install.sh file.

This follows https://review.openstack.org/#/c/508061 to remove
tools/tox_install.sh.

Change-Id: I3a6c85db180c25e360934ada60df7328ed7a765a
(cherry picked from commit 5e13aaca2c94c6f665f46230ae5c353955d7208c)

commit_message:
Fix async keyword for Python 3.7

In Python 3.7, async becomes a keyword, and therefore we need
to change variable async. This patch renames async into async_ .

Change-Id: I46486e74b6c8fe03baa415f83d9bdaf4ce4994eb

commit_message:
remove mention of rootwrap from data file list

Commit 3023edd70ae58c0f45ecebbe4048c95d3d4ebe8d removed the
rootwrap.conf file but did not update the packaging manifest. That means
we can no longer build packages of glance, and that is breaking the
requirements-integration job in the openstack/requirements repository.
This change removes the mention of the file so the packaging step
doesn't try to include a file that is not there.

Change-Id: I94d17416e6290fd2d047d7401f22a719b82c8945
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Stop hardcoding baremetal API version in stackrc

Long time ago it was required because ironicclient defaulted to
an ancient version. It was changed back in Queens (ironicclient 2.0),
so we can drop it now to avoid confusion.

Change-Id: Icea0bdf6d5dcdd81ce9c34be7af8a241da0861bc
Closes-Bug: #1789392

commit_message:
Remove fdb entries for ha router interfaces when going DOWN

When HA router's interface on host is going DOWN but router
is still available on this host, L2 population
mechanism driver will now send to other hosts info to remove
fdb unicast entries to this port on host.

It will not send FLOODING_ENTRY because this port is still on
host but in standby mode and might be transformed to master
in future.

This solves issue with migration router from Legacy to HA.
In such case, port which was originally attached to legacy
router is transformed to be HA backup port before changing
its status to DOWN.
Now in such case unicast entries to this port and backup
node will be removed properly so packets to HA router will
be really send to host which is master node for router.

Closes-Bug: #1785582

Change-Id: Icc14e5f5d40fc6fbb49e0f7b18cc3b15ebec8508
(cherry picked from commit 6c300b1a9b3f0db82b4edd84eda74600d28b7185)

commit_message:
Trivial: Remove app_conf kwarg from testing setup

The RestfulTestCase classes in both rest.py and test_v3.py both
defined an app_conf kwarg in their setUp() method signatures that
was never used. This commit removes app_conf since it doesn't make
sense to define it if it's not used.

Change-Id: Ide8303363c662747e1527f7de553dba40606986e

commit_message:
List soft-deleted instances by "--status" option

Using "nova list --status SOFT_DELETED" cannot get soft-deleted instances.
Because sqlalchemy will filter out SOFT_DELETED instances in
instance_get_all_by_filters_sort without considering vm_state filter
passed by nova-api.

Change-Id: Id2d72c0c71f1d862d5192d4ac985e4fbd27a4438
Closes-bug: #1789455

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

commit_message:
WIP: Attempt to speed up plan template processing

Major refactoring of the ProcessTemplatesAction. Now utilizes the Swift
Service, in order to batch things up a bit. Still needs to rework the
upload portion.

Some tests disabled for now to get an integration test to happen. Will
fix before full merge.

commit_message:
Remove job settings for monasca-agent

Python 3.5 was wrongly enabled for all branches. They always break on
branches older than stable/rocky because of dependency of supervisor
package that did not had version working with Python 3.

Also remove Python 2 jobs as Zuul config for every branche soon will be
merged to respective branches.

Change-Id: I9dcdc2fc8fdb78552c87004bd02a5b513f60742a

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: If5fc68369bb8fc629e35e926008254e864100d6f

commit_message:
Document no content on POST /reshaper 204

For consistency with other 204-returning operations in the placement API
reference, mention that POST /reshaper returns no body content on
success.

FUP from https://review.openstack.org/#/c/576927/35/placement-api-ref/source/reshaper.inc@45

Change-Id: I50dda0b161404d96dae35a3a96225f1ac4ec7309

"}, {'created': '2018-07-16 11:24:48.000000000', 'message': 'WIP: [placement] Add /reshaper handler for POST

/reshaper provides a way to atomically modify some allocations and
inventory in a single transaction, allowing operations like migrating
some inventory from a parent provider to a new child.

A fair amount of code is reused from handler/inventory.py, some
refactoring is in order before things get too far with that.

In handler/allocation.py some code is extracted to its own methods
so it can be reused from reshaper.py.

This is done as microversion 1.30, but at this stage seems likely
that will need to change.

There are a small number of gabbi tests, but additional tests will be
required to fully cover the various error conditions and success models.
The tests that are there thus far were mostly created to validate the
JSON schema.

Change-Id: I5b33ac3572bc3789878174ffc86ca42ae8035cfa

In handler/allocation.py some code is extracted to its own methods
so it can be reused from reshaper.py.

This is done as microversion 1.30, but at this stage seems likely
that will need to change.

There are a small number of gabbi tests, but additional tests will be
required to fully cover the various error conditions and success models.

Change-Id: I5b33ac3572bc3789878174ffc86ca42ae8035cfa

commit_message:
[placement] Add /reshaper handler for POST

/reshaper provides a way to atomically modify some allocations and
inventory in a single transaction, allowing operations like migrating
some inventory from a parent provider to a new child.

A fair amount of code is reused from handler/inventory.py, some
refactoring is in order before things get too far with that.

In handler/allocation.py some code is extracted to its own methods
so it can be reused from reshaper.py.

This is done as microversion 1.30.

A suite of gabbi tests is provided which attempt to cover various
failures including schema violations, generation conflicts, and
data conflicts.

api-ref, release notes and rest history are updated

Change-Id: I5b33ac3572bc3789878174ffc86ca42ae8035cfa
Partially-Implements: blueprint reshape-provider-tree

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I7332a020602c3171825e842df7d23dc4950eb597

commit_message:
Simplify tenacity sleep mocking

This changes the tenacity sleep mocking to not rely on tenacity
internals, and to mock for all tests so that slow tests are not
accidently missed.

Change-Id: I0519e5e1c0edc1f2192a011f9fa524b5380d3518
Related-Bug: #1788802

commit_message:
Add new COE API endpoint

This patch adds the new /v1/coe endpoint to the API that can be
used to list the COEs and their supported network and volume drivers
where the network drivers is also filtered on the allowed drivers.

There is no logic in Magnum right now that acts as a manager for the
COEs so they are somewhat hardcoded right now but as long as the format
of the new endpoint is OK we can always clean that up.

Change-Id: I507aee928f0d0b13c2e9d2fb4a23911bdb90f1d0
Story: 2003548
Task: 24835
Related-Bug: 1568890

commit_message:
Remove usage of nova's RamFilter

As of https://review.openstack.org/596502/ in Stein
the RamFilter in nova is deprecated. It is not needed
when using the filter_scheduler driver (which is the
default scheduler driver).

Change-Id: Iee3dab7b5dc7074e9840826afe58ce2bfa40a3df

commit_message:
Enable Ansible error handling per role

Enable Ansible group_yar options to be set per TripleO role.
Initially supporting any_errors_fatal and max_fail_percentage
this change provides a structure by which future per-role Ansible
options can readily be added to group_vars.

Change-Id: I6792bccbd090b04d63bcef07bdb936a9685864c5
Closes-Bug: 1760989
Depends-On: I47954717f42f14bae8d9fd2bd17cd8ea1fd787b3

commit_message:
Make openstack undercloud upgrade --dry-run actually dry

--dry-run wasn't previously honored with openstack undercloud upgrade
and the upgrade ran anyway.

Change-Id: Iea0c78b021cf5b83c5b5fa66e52b9e50ecc291a9
Closes-Bug: #1788047

commit_message:
Use luminous for Debian Stretch

There's no Mimic Debian repository available upstream for Stretch.
Therefore, stick with Luminous until we have something better to play with.

Change-Id: Id98df19700d111ff919b8b3ac5db88cec07f7b59

commit_message:

upon kuryr-controller restart, ensuring previously created ports
are re-used.

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

commit_message:
Don't use '_TransactionContextManager._async'

In commit 2d532963, all instances of 'async' were replaced with 'async_'
in preparation for Python 3.7. However, one of these should not have
been changed as it refers to an oslo.db object attribute. That attribute
has actually been renamed itself but that rename is only present from
oslo.db 4.40.0 [1]. Thankfully, an alias to the older name is provided
so we use that.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/oslo.db/commit/df6bf34

Change-Id: I1afd0ba34a9ebcb63edb91e880ef60580befb32e
Closes-Bug: #1788833

commit_message:
Ceph update and upgrade in config-download era

Correct playbook selection is now done automatically using
external_update_tasks and external_upgrade_tasks. The
CephAnsiblePlaybook is still usable and highest priority if set to
something else than the default. It can also be set to [] to
completely skip ceph-ansible playbook execution.

Closes-Bug: #1783949
Change-Id: If7955b31eda432dd61331281ad3d8f25a335fdfe
Depends-On: Ifdf5f1175849f79b98c76b4bcdef2a70f8f1fedb

commit_message:
Systematically skip test_get_rated_tenants test

With the current tempest plugin, no data is pushed to cloudkitty's storage
backend, so the API returns no rated tenants.

Change-Id: Id434bc72d9625d557833838025549dc672856334

commit_message:
Revert "Add a default rootwrap.conf file."

glance_store is a dependency of glance, has the actual
cinder integration code and ships a rootwrap.conf file,
as well as the required filters and glance-rootwrap
binary, so drop rootwrap.conf from glance.

This reverts commit 01fa437b94e95194ef451f50b0cb6eefc3030759.

Change-Id: I50cacdd7edeef204eef93c1d3338f420a3aa0216

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I8a9455ab1e2ad399d65a10433333f184fc99a130

commit_message:
Remove "async" as variable name

In Python 3.7, async becomes a language keyword. Let's rename this
local variable from "async" to "async_sup" to be Py 3.7 compatible.

Change-Id: I56c9876ecc7e567ccc7a781073494aee00bb099d

commit_message:
Drop nose dependencies

Horizon test setting no longer depends on nose and related stuffs.
This commit cleans up nose related dependencies.

Also drops unnecessary Django dependencies. There is no need to
install Django explicitly as it is a horizon dependency.

Change-Id: I33091ef3c85ccff835f5995c668a9894454d182b

remove job settings for Oslo repositories

This is a mechanically generated patch to remove the job settings that
have been migrated to the git repositories owned by the Oslo team.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Story: #2003250
Change-Id: I3476584f37402431787aabbce1d0c7bf37cebeee

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I49c3912a6eed81d896442e012354efe952aa2000
Story: #2002586
Task: #24298

commit_message:
Fix the undefined method 'chomp' for nil:NilClass error seen with ovs 2.10

puppet-ovn uses puppet-vswitch to configure the OVN params. When OVS binaries are
compiled with dpdk support and when vs_config provider runs the command
'ovs-vsctl list Open_vSwitch .', the below warning messages are seen and
are part of the command output.

----
PMD: net_mlx5: cannot load glue library: libibverbs.so.1: cannot open shared
object file: No such file or directory
PMD: net_mlx5: cannot initialize PMD due to missing run-time dependency on
rdma-core libraries (libibverbs, libmlx5)
----

We see the error 'undefined method 'chomp' for nil:NilClass' when the result is
extracted. This patch fixes this issue by checking if the 'value' var is nil or
not before 'parse_column_value' is called.

Tripleo deployment with OVN is failing because of this issue.

Change-Id: I415a6229a0fbc1b55451e3738539735afdc6f8f4
Closes-bug: #1789236

commit_message:
Add a check to ignore the unmatched lines from ovs-vsctl command

Provider vs_config is failing if unmatched lines are see as the
output of ovs-vsctl command. In some case, warnings generated
doesn't match the pattern, which is causing this error. Add a
check to ignore the unmatched lines.

Change-Id: Ic07f3d61273b9622a6bad097af24c7e617230c10

Thanks a lot for the reviews, the consideration are just theoretical now, but since we are going to use this in our public cloud and it will be high possibility of current requests, and lock on read will degrade the performance a little bit for sure.'}, {'account_id': 4393, 'date': '2018-08-23 17:19:12.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

> Thanks a lot for the reviews, the consideration are just
 > theoretical now, but since we are going to use this in our public
 > cloud and it will be high possibility of current requests, and lock
 > on read will degrade the performance a little bit for sure.

I don't think this is the case. Since we're using @synchronized(), we take the default of external=False, which means the lock is confined to our process. So any worker process will only use the lock to protect against eventlet threads within that process from taking the lock at the same time. Once a given cell has made it into the cache, we don't do anything schedule-able in the locked section, and since only one eventlet thread is actually executing at any given time, there's no way for there to be contention. Thus, aside from when readers need to be locked out (when one writer thread is populating the cache) I think the lock is a no-op.

Am I missing something?"}, {'account_id': 15888, 'date': '2018-08-24 02:09:44.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

 > at any given time, there's no way for there to be contention. Thus,
 > aside from when readers need to be locked out (when one writer
 > thread is populating the cache) I think the lock is a no-op.
 > 
 > Am I missing something?

Hi, thanks for the clarification, but I'm tend to think this lock is useless now. As you mentioned, the ``external`` is ``False`` which means different API workers will not be locked for this action, which makes the comment in line 362 is incorrect, and as you mentioned, this locks things up for eventlets in same process, and in the case we actually doing this, we are scattering across cells, and the cell uuid is actually different, so there will be no 2 eventlets access one lock, and since one API worker can only response one request at a time, seems this lock doesn't have any functionality at all."}, {'account_id': 4393, 'date': '2018-08-24 13:42:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

> Hi, thanks for the clarification, but I'm tend to think this lock
 > is useless now. As you mentioned, the ``external`` is ``False``
 > which means different API workers will not be locked for this
 > action, which makes the comment in line 362 is incorrect, and as
 > you mentioned, this locks things up for eventlets in same process,
 > and in the case we actually doing this, we are scattering across
 > cells, and the cell uuid is actually different, so there will be no
 > 2 eventlets access one lock, and since one API worker can only
 > response one request at a time, seems this lock doesn't have any
 > functionality at all.

No, it does, but the comment is misleading.

In eventlet, only one thread runs at a time until some schedule-able event happens, at which time we switch threads (cooperative multitasking). So, s/workers/eventlet threads/ in that comment. Multiple API worker *processes* aren't excluded from running at the same time, but they don't need to be since CELL_CACHE is not shared between them. However, it is shared between eventlet threads within a single worker. When the first one comes along to check the cache and determines it is empty, it will (with the lock held) start the process of creating the transport and database connections. These involve IO to those servers and thus are schedule-able events. If we didn't have the lock, then any eventlet threads racing to do this check would (or could) all simultaneously find an empty cache, create connections of their own, and only one would "win" by being last to store its connections in the cache. That is the situation the lock is trying to exclude.

Once the cache is populated, there aren't any schedule-able events in the process of checking the cache and targeting the context, and thus the lock becomes effectively a no-op since threads can't race in that region.'}, {'account_id': 4690, 'date': '2018-08-24 15:27:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
Only lock when race condition happens in context.set_target_cell

Currently when doing set_target_cell() we lock both read and
write operation, as the lock is added to prevent create duplicated
db and mq connection, but actually this only happens in the ``write``
process, we can only lock when race condition happens to increase
the overall performance a little bit.

Change-Id: I03077af6ea2726099e24920f973b028895380991
Closes-Bug: #1788564

commit_message:
Add container prepare step to Standalone

Let's reuse the container image prepare default command to generate the
container prepare items rather than hard coding it in the
standalone_parameters.yaml. This is closer to what we would expect a
user to do for the overcloud or is automatically done during the
undercloud installation.

Change-Id: Ibdc8e7a034ee5a07c75fc1423a2266bc93d3fcb0

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I75140c349be76da9df931e90e18c79b15692bd0b

commit_message:
Avoids calling ffi.dlopen(None) on Windows

ffi.dlopen(None) cannot work on Windows and it is a
known issue [1]. This patch avoids this call on Windows
hosts.

[1] https://bugs.python.org/issue23606

Change-Id: I44436146cdc402087f33f4b99054176134ec5b81
Closes-Bug: #1788025
(cherry picked from commit b1f50df3b1cde1b8c770d810e201077aa1bec921)

commit_message:
Trivial: avoid KeyError while processing ports

The Neutron OVS agent logs can get flooded with KeyErrors as the
'_get_port_info' method skips the added/removed dict items if no
ports have been added/removed, which are expected to be present,
even if those are just empty sets.

This change ensures that those port info dict fields are always set.

Closes-Bug: #1783556

Change-Id: I9e5325aa2d8525231353ba451e8ea895be51b1ca
(cherry picked from commit da5b13df2b2a8171f60311414250671820390738)

commit_message:
Modify abandon_old_reviews script

This script can now check and abandon old patches only from
specified project.
Project must be one of Neutron deliverables.
Project can be passed to script with parameter:
"--project <project_name>"

If no project is specified it will get old patches from all projects
which are part of neutron stadium.

Change-Id: I83b9a556d551db9f78b3d628df8648309e1dda1d

commit_message:
Fix package function update with same md5

Do not update or delete the function package if updating the function
with the same package but not providing the md5.

Story: 2003482

commit_message:
Use older keepalived version in functional tests

It looks that current keepalived version which is available in
Ubuntu Xenial repositories (1:1.2.24-1ubuntu0.16.04.1) is broken
and cause failure of some functional tests in Neutron.
Details are in [1].
Older version works fine so as temporary solution we can use
this version in functional tests.

This issue don't happens on master and stable/rocky branch, as there
newer cloud-archive repo is used and it has newer version of keepalived
which works fine.

[1] https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/keepalived/+bug/1789045

Change-Id: I418a967cd503991736e72134d4a105b6e97021e8
Closes-Bug: #1788185

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-03 13:20:50.000000000', 'message': 'Remove base class complex and confusing variable

neutron base class have base create method like create_network,
create_routers, create_port and create_subnets etc and these
base method append the created resources in base class variable
like cls.ports, cls.sunets etc.

These variable were initially  created and used while cleanup the
created resources in corresponding delete methods. But now those
delete methods has been switched to use addClassResourceCleanup.

commit_message:
Remove base class complex and confusing variable

neutron base class have base create method like create_network,
create_routers, create_port and create_subnets etc and these
base method append the created resources in base class variable
like cls.ports, cls.sunets etc.

These variable were initially  created and used while cleanup the
created resources in corresponding delete methods. But now those
delete methods has been switched to use addClassResourceCleanup.

Few test class still use them for list resources etc which is
hard to find that these were from base class and value is being
populated from derived class test cases.

This commit removes the base class variables and define those
in derived test class wherever they are being used.

Change-Id: I24fdfbdb8a2d7bcb4ccab8e57f1967b13f35f184

commit_message:
Revert "Revert "Work around nested virt issues on OVH test nodes""

Instances are failing to launch on OVH in Tempest runs with the following:
KVM: entry failed, hardware error 0x0

Octavia team reporting the same.

This reverts commit 16cf0de8a4c362181b7ea5709db2bb7eae4d0931.

Change-Id: I8a47d88fdb24ea0dd2f259103c23527e8c877211

commit_message:
Allow extension of volumes with snapshots for VZstorage driver

This change lifts an earlier limitation that explicitely did
not extend a volume if snapshots of that volume exist. This
limitation was lifted on the glusterfs driver and this change
mirrors that behaviour.

Partial-bug: #1687048

Change-Id: I9aa727b1880b374105c2cad685dc196c7d39f841

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
