(5 comments)

I would like it to be considered whether this should go under oslo_utils.uuidutils instead. You know, given that it's a UUID util.

(If it does, a lock should be imposed around the bit where we generate a new UUID and add it to the cache - for thread safety in case it gets used for some non-test purpose.)"}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2018-08-21 12:21:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

(2 comments)'}, {'account_id': 11564, 'date': '2018-08-21 12:27:41.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

One thing I've wondered about this is whether we need to have any concerns about collisions in the names and whether those concerns change at all when uuidsentinels are coming from a library like this.

I assume not, since the breadth and lifecycle of of the test process and use of names is the same as it ever was.

Very often we use names like uuids.rp1 and it is okay because we are cleaning up things like the database between tests (even though the underlying uuid remains the same).

So yeah, fine.

Nothing to add beyond the comments other people have already mentioned."}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2018-08-21 13:58:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

> I would like it to be considered whether this should go under oslo_utils.uuidutils instead.

I proposed that alternative [1] for dicsussion, and hopefully addressed most of the concerns raised in this version.

commit_message:
Add uuidsentinel test module

This adds a module that behaves like mock.sentinel, but that
returns UUIDs suitable for use in tests where we need that
specifically.

This code is from [1], but have some difference:
1. The enforced-singleton stuff is removed [2], and the
_UUIDSentinels class is private and a uuids instance is exposed.
2. Add some doc strings for it.

There is an alternate patch [2] in oslo.utils.

This module is used by Nova and Placement, so we extract it
into oslotest library.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/722d5b4/nova/tests/uuidsentinel.py
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/594179

Co-Authored-By: Eric Fried <efried@us.ibm.com>

Change-Id: I2c8914c45a2b60f2f90b97fc6a1b22809d85f972

commit_message:
Start booting instances at vexxhost-sjc1

This starts by booting only 10 instances to start with a small
sanity check to make sure everything is working well.  The
number will be bumped up once things are running well.

Change-Id: I196c1a5a53f314632644f31b54debbc016ab8b5e

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: Ib72b23fb58f17e39a8d4accc97308921826efd6b

commit_message:
Revert "Don't use '_TransactionContextManager._async'"

This reverts commit bd7d991309ea2bea5d175cb1f2710519936fd0c2 and bumps
the minimum version of oslo.db to 4.40.0, as that is the first version
of the library to include the renamed attribute.

Change-Id: Ic9e7864be3af7ef362cad5648dfc7bdecd104465
Related-Bug: #1788833

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I84d6d32e970c1e1866a5ad5c216d7e926ccd8135

commit_message:
Fetch images again inside BM undercloud playbook

While splitting the baremetal job we forgot to include the fetch-images
part with the result of failing deploys. This commit fix the issue re
introducing the role at the end of the baremetal undercloud preparation.

Change-Id: Ic03473f5bb7d44d0a92257ce6d035a805322a8c2

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I91de5a7fb16e9bbf944514ada995812eab155b1c

commit_message:
Add distinct conf opt groups for both validation methodologies

This patchset adds a distinct group for each of the validation
methodologies:

  * oslo.policy approach => policy_validation
  * custom requirements approach => requirements_validation

policy_validation receives the following options:

  * custom_policy_files

requirements_validation receives the following options:

  * custom_requirements_file
  * test_custom_requirements

Background: In the initial Patrole spec for project creation submitted
to qa-specs [0] there is much discussion about oslo.policy-driven vs.
requirements-driven approach to RBAC validation. Long story short:
Patrole by default does oslo.policy validation but later added
requirements-driven validation [1]. However, the options for both
ways of doing validation should be made as distinct as possible to
avoid confusion between which options to use for which validation
methods.

[0] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/382672/
[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/477014/

Change-Id: I2f3205976fb7f690f967cb30570ed9b1bec8293f

commit_message:
Fix default value for overcloud_roles

This commit prevent errors like [1] that you'll get when you don't
define the "overcloud_roles" variable while declaring instead:

composable_roles: true
generate_overcloud_roles: "Controller ComputeInstanceHA"

ansible will process the template in any case, despite the when condition
turning false, making the task fail.

[1] "AnsibleUndefinedVariable: 'overcloud_roles' is undefined

Change-Id: I5218c6b65e62d58a2346e95026c1ca2fb4f0d8f9

[{'created': '2018-07-30 11:41:45.000000000', 'message': 'Remove tripleo.sh --bootstrap-subnodes from toci_gate_test.sh

In https://review.openstack.org/583195 we are removing the bootstrap
subnodes invocations for the zuul v3 jobs and the templated version
of toci_gate_test.sh.j2. Here we do the same for the legacy bash
version of toci_gate_test.sh and add a deprecation note on the
tripleo.sh --bootstrap-subnodes function itself.

The invocation of tripleo.sh is removed with the now unused functions
echo_vars_to_deploy_env_oooq subnodes_scp_deploy_env

Instead the creation of ceph /dev/loop3 is handled in the base job
pre.yaml added in the Depends-On below

Depends-On: https://review.rdoproject.org/r/15000
Change-Id: I039388e4c3d4959270c45e827e76993636bd2990

commit_message:
Remove tripleo.sh --bootstrap-subnodes from toci_gate_test.sh

In https://review.openstack.org/583195 we are removing the bootstrap
subnodes invocations for the zuul v3 jobs and the templated version
of toci_gate_test.sh.j2. Here we do the same for the legacy bash
version of toci_gate_test.sh and add a deprecation note on the
tripleo.sh --bootstrap-subnodes function itself.

The invocation of tripleo.sh is removed with the now unused functions
echo_vars_to_deploy_env_oooq subnodes_scp_deploy_env

Instead the creation of ceph /dev/loop3 is handled in the base job
pre.yaml added in the Depends-On below

Depends-On: https://review.rdoproject.org/r/15000
Depends-On: Ib95b02767488aaddfe95633d03cb118dd492a700
Change-Id: I039388e4c3d4959270c45e827e76993636bd2990

import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:

commit_message:
Allow tags prefixed with v in default regex

The version scheme v1.0.0 is not an uncommon way to tag versions
and used to be part of the semver spec. This patch allows the
optional v prefix in the default version scheme.

ref: https://github.com/semver/semver/blob/master/semver.md#is-v123-a-semantic-version

Change-Id: I4a99bda8b788ee5fd2a8aca3463eb548d07f1313
Signed-off-by: Thanh Ha <zxiiro@linux.com>

commit_message:
Remove deprecated `tls-ca-file` option from kube-apiserver

tls-ca-file flag is unused and was removed from kube-apiserver
in kubernetes 1.11. This means that any cluster with this
option specified will fail on apiserver start
Pull request on flag removal:
https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/61386

Task: 24858
Story: 2003566

Change-Id: I9c192b94056629a949ee92d867e8cda5c4ff6810

commit_message:
Handle missing endpoint_data in maximum_supported_microversions

Apparently, for standalone case get_endpoint_data can
1. Raise an exception in case of e.g. versioned baremetal endpoint
2. Return None

This change inserts safeguards for both cases.

Change-Id: Iea9f5f576519f0bec7ba0f2edc6106f5780c5465

commit_message:
Fix crash on Service catalog empty 403 response

Added handling of message body received as bytes ("application/json")
to avoid "TypeError: the JSON object must be str, not 'bytes'"

Change-Id: I007b33e1b9f210ede2df5d1e2aa32535222d5d67
Task:24818
Story: 2003533
Signed-off-by: Boris Pilka <boris.pilka@x-works.io>

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Also change fetch-stestr-output to fetch-subunit-output, since the role
was apparently renamed.

Make castellan-functional-devstack temporarily non-voting for now to be
able to continue with python3-first move - followup change will make it
voting again.

Change-Id: I5c31e7d77765dacaafbf1f56552eed848a18bf55
Story: #2003250

commit_message:
Remove legacy-install-afs-with-puppet role

This role uses the system-config:install_puppet.sh script to first
install puppet on the wheel-builder host, and then uses
puppet-kerberos/puppet-openafs to bring up the AFS environment.

This is replaced with ansible roles to do the same AFS bring-up.  A
new "openafs-client" playbook is added to configure this for the infra
environment.  The wheel-building base job is reworked to use this.

Roles have been tested under zuul with
https://review.openstack.org/596018

kerberos-client role:
Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/593486
openafs-client role:
Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/593487
add system-config to linters:
Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/596645
Change-Id: I9a3af36048e4a4439fe86b36582667ff0af68035

commit_message:
Optimize global marker re-lookup in multi_cell_list

Now that we have cell_uuid stashed on RequestContext, we can avoid
looking up the global marker again in the thread that matches
that cell. This removes one unnecessary lookup-by-value of the marker
value we already have and the associated FIXME.

Change-Id: Id1a0538de4cc3235680579ffa0ecf7f4eb24a1dd

commit_message:
Drop version from OS_AUTH_URL

We're configuring OS_IDENTITY_API_VERSION so the /v3 is not really
necessary. Additionally, the string replace being used is resulting in a
// in the url.

Depends-On: Ia41d21ebad9329ae9fa506868957a72e6f9a5ca5
Change-Id: Id8f2ec0d78eec7276b7d4f82782d64e4edde6302
Closes-Bug: #1785660

commit_message:
Add zuul roles in system-config to linters

Add zuul roles defined in system-config to the
openstack-zuul-jobs-linters job.  Playbooks in project-config will
require the generic roles that live in system-config.

Change-Id: I0156ed16e2a165493227df5ea51561aad897c65b
Needed-By: https://review.openstack.org/590636

commit_message:
Don't invoke multiple migration requests for single vm.

This is Pike only fix. If there are multiple migration requests
for the same instance, the placement inventory might
not be cleaned up in time, leading to further migration requests
to this compute to fail:
  <snip>
  Allocation for VCPU on resource provider
  b6d1973f-bc39-4ea0-8d28-15f988f762e1 violates min_unit, max_unit,
    or step_size. Requested: 5, min_unit: 1, max_unit: 4, step_size: 1
  Placement API returning an error response:
   Unable to allocate inventory:
    Unable to create allocation for 'VCPU' on resource provider
     The requested amount would violate inventory constraints

Change migration timeout to 180 seconds.
Both nova-compute and neutron-openvswitch-agent have to be up to
have live-migration working. Added check for neutron's part.

Closes-Bug: 1785568
Change-Id: If46c43aee9a409b59f2dcb139d739106bc9a562f

As the original author and heavy user of this code, I just want to throw my -1 on here. Having to instantiate the UUIDSentinels object in every place this gets used, and having it not be a singleton defeats the behaves-like-mock.sentinel usefulness of this code.

Sounds like this is happening regardless, and I expect we'll just paper over this in nova so that it behaves properly. I don't understand why we're breaking this just because someone thought we need to use uuidutils for the generation."}, {'account_id': 2472, 'date': '2018-08-27 17:07:33.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

We said in the meeting we would keep the global, but not the bit of code that modifies sys.modules. I think that still allows it to be used via a simple import, doesn't it?"}, {'account_id': 4393, 'date': '2018-08-27 17:16:55.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

> We said in the meeting we would keep the global, but not the bit of
 > code that modifies sys.modules. I think that still allows it to be
 > used via a simple import, doesn't it?

No, it does not. Unless the instance of UUIDSentinel replaces the module (or a module) the __getattr__ does not get hit until you instantiate it. That means the following does not work:

 from whatever import uuidsentinel
 my_uuid = uuidsentinel.thing

which is how mock.sentinel works.

I will also point out that there are places in base nova test infrastructure that set up complicated structures like default cells layouts, etc. These use uuidsentinel.cell1 for example, which tests in other files sometimes need to refer to in order to disambiguate targeted calls deep in a stack. We would have to either (a) change how that stuff works, (b) keep our own sys.modules override with the oslo utils thing underneath, or (c) just keep our uuidsentinel implementation and ignore this one."}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2018-08-27 17:43:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Workflow-1

Okay, I missed that restoring the global was deemed okay, which I think would allow the usage Dan points out. [{'created': '2018-08-21 13:53:51.000000000', 'message': "UUID sentinel

Add a uuidsentinel singleton to oslo_utils.uuidutils that behaves like a
mock.sentinel, but returns specifically UUIDs. This is mostly copied
from [1], with the following differences:

- We don't do the enforced-singleton thing [2]. The _UUIDSentinels class
  is private and a uuidsentinels instance is exposed.
- We don't do the local import thing [3][4], because... we're already in
  there.
- Locking is added to make this threadsafe. (See discussion at [5])

Note that there is some question as to whether it is more appropriate
for this to live here or in oslotest [6]. Considerations:

- As a UUID util, it makes sense for it to live in a module called
  uuidutils.
- We can avoid circular import problems (oslotest requires oslo_utils;
  uuidsentinel uses oslo_utils.uuidutils.generate_uuid()) if it lives
  here.
- If it's used exclusively for testing, oslotest makes sense. I can't
  think of a use outside of test offhand, but I didn't try too hard -
  I'm sure somebody will. Thread safety was the only concern with this
  being general-purpose, and that has been addressed here.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/722d5b477219f0a2435a9f4ad4d54c61b83219f1/nova/tests/uuidsentinel.py

commit_message:
UUID sentinel

Add a private _UUIDSentinels() class to oslo_utils.fixture that behaves
like a mock.sentinel, but returns specifically UUIDs. Expose a
(singleton) instance of it called uuidsentinel. This is mostly copied
from [1], with the following differences:

- We don't do the enforced-singleton thing [2]. But importing the
  uuidsentinel global yields the same behavior.
- We don't do the local import thing [3][4], because we're already in
  the right lib, so no issues with circular imports.
- Locking is added to make this threadsafe. (See discussion at [5])

Note that there is some question as to whether it is more appropriate
for this to live here or in oslotest [6]. This has been discussed on the
dev ML [7] and it was concluded [8] that it should live here.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/722d5b477219f0a2435a9f4ad4d54c61b83219f1/nova/tests/uuidsentinel.py
[2] https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/722d5b477219f0a2435a9f4ad4d54c61b83219f1/nova/tests/uuidsentinel.py#L30

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-05-25 21:20:19.000000000', 'message': 'Improve time_check output

The local request start and end times (combined with jitter, if
provided) define a window of tolerable remote times. When the remote
time falls outside of that window, output the delta to get *within* the
window rather than the delta to get *to the end* of the window.

Additionally, output both the starting and ending local time if they
format differently; this avoids confusing output when the request takes
a while to complete and the remote has a time before the local time.

Change-Id: Ifa450ba518b0c823889455c97fa093a2fa0073b4
Related-Change: I4891397e7cc0817819201b361f79f8fe7fdcfc89
'}]
commit_message:
Improve time_check output

The local request start and end times (combined with jitter, if
provided) define a window of tolerable remote times. When the remote
time falls outside of that window, output the delta to get *within* the
window rather than the delta to get *to the end* of the window.

Additionally, output both the starting and ending local time if they
format differently; this avoids confusing output when the request takes
a while to complete and the remote has a time before the local time.

Change-Id: Ifa450ba518b0c823889455c97fa093a2fa0073b4
Related-Change: I4891397e7cc0817819201b361f79f8fe7fdcfc89

commit_message:
Bump upstream Rocky repos

There is an issue with the version of tempest present in the
constraints file from the requirements repo on stable/rocky branch.

This updates the upstream shas to the latest version so that
tempest gets bumped to 19.0.0, which would allow to skip our
hacks in the rocky branch.

Change-Id: I93bfa917d0d56ea02c3bcc2b09e9b92365d6b04c

commit_message:
Drop SELinux support for CentOS 7

We do not have a maintainer at the moment for SELinux and hopefully
we will adopt the upstream openstack-selinux package, but for now
in order to let deploys in environments where SELinux is set to
permissive work, we'll have to remove these bits.

This change can be reverted whenever we have a maintainer that's
available to do the work required.

Change-Id: I4c7b6a9c0d8ec1458a9396422d047e1327bb4d45
(cherry picked from commit d5bd0791fe874860d31b351584fc37539875370b)

commit_message:
Fix the RFC and private internet network address

It seems the RFC should be 1918 which defines IP addresses for private
networks.

The existing RFC 5737 actually defines private IP ranges for use in
documentation.

Change-Id: Ic794585e636bb9a9c915347a801c8a4f0baa9012
Closes-Bug: 1788936

commit_message:
Record cell success/failure/timeout in CrossCellLister

This makes it easier to handle the cells that failed from layers
above, by reporting the cell uuids that reported, failed, and
timed out.

Related to blueprint handling-down-cell
Change-Id: Ied2264982a713bd27351eb690dd47f8531485d4f

commit_message:
Update all SHAs for 15.1.27

This patch:
- updates all the roles to the latest available stable SHAs
- copies the release notes from the updated roles into the integrated repo
- updates all the OpenStack Service SHAs

Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/595356
Change-Id: I5976c3416ccd626228e1da87f68acc345dff0089

commit_message:
pbrx upload: remove protected flag

This job is designed to be modified by other projects.  Its security
currently depends on the allowed-projects setting.  Remove the
protected flag which doesn't make sense in that case.

Change-Id: Iefe6bd4457b0616352e86d110cc1680ee0626ddb

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: Iaa1add7f6155d28200429d8be3f3de70b3224329
Story: #2002586
Task: #24295

members of the instance group if the RequestContext is untargeted, else
it queries the targeted cell for the instances.

commit_message:
Make scheduler.utils.setup_instance_group query all cells

To check affinity and anti-affinity policies for scheduling instances,
we use the RequestSpec.instance_group.hosts field to check the hosts
that have group members on them. Access of the 'hosts' field calls
InstanceGroup.get_hosts during a lazy-load and get_hosts does a query
for all instances that are members of the group and returns their hosts
after removing duplicates. The InstanceList query isn't targeting any
cells, so it will return [] in a multi-cell environment in both the
instance create case and the instance move case. In the move case, we
do have a cell-targeted RequestContext when setup_instance_group is
called *but* the RequestSpec.instance_group object is queried early in
compute/api before we're targeted to a cell, so a call of
RequestSpec.instance_group.get_hosts() will result in [] still, even
for move operations.

This makes setup_instance_group query all cells for instances that are
members of the instance group if the RequestContext is untargeted, else
it queries the targeted cell for the instances.

Closes-Bug: #1746863

Change-Id: Ia5f5a0d75953b1154a8de3e1eaa15f8042e32d77

commit_message:
Handle DiscoveryFailure errors

DiscoveryFailures can happen for a variety of reasons, ranging
from service misconfiguration to a keystone outage to a transient
network failure. If we don't catch and handle the failure here,
it will almost certainly cause something further up the WSGI stack
to send a 500 Internal Error (and likely log a traceback).

A log line like

    Unable to validate token: Could not find versioned identity
    endpoints when attempting to authenticate. Please check that
    your auth_url is correct. Unable to establish connection to
    http://keystone:35357: HTTPConnectionPool(host='keystone',
    port=35357): Max retries exceeded with url: / (Caused by
    NewConnectionError('<urllib3.connection.HTTPConnection
    object at 0x7fc53e22e050>: Failed to establish a new
    connection: [Errno 111] ECONNREFUSED',))

should be plenty enough for an operator to assess the situation;
I don't need a 29-frame traceback.

Change-Id: I946388c09b2ca0230d2cef009c679a7ac7c8398f

commit_message:
Refactor repo_cmd_before

* curl --silent was replaced with curl -sSL --conect-timeout=60
  -s - short version of --silent, -S - --show-errors, -L - --location
  --conect-timeout sets connection timeout to 60 as curl doesn't set any
  default timeouts
* Add -z conditional logic for master-undercloud-pike-overcloud.yml
* Improve bash syntax
* docker_registry_namespace value was replaced with {{ release }}

Change-Id: I71789bff2f63654f2363b66ad6e271efb0b20817

commit_message:
Add makestep to chronyd config.

This change will adjust the clock at once if the clock is offsetted for more
than 1 sec when chronyd starts.

Change-Id: Ia8bb5d2b75dfbff33eb7de3a293d943632e6860e
(cherry picked from commit 0c4b71f49464583a390fe1dc49c4cc73b22990ac)

commit_message:
Fix deprecation warnings for te-broker

As a technical debt this change replaces "heat stack-show" with "openstack stack
show" as well as "heat stack-delete" with "openstack stack delete" to remove
deprecation warnings such as 'WARNING (shell) "heat stack-show" is deprecated,
please use "openstack stack show"' for te-broker.

Change-Id: I3df881371a0a3c283a0ac5456cc282f865d1897f

commit_message:
VMAX doc - important known issue

A ucode upgrade on an VMAX All Flash will cause issues if
workloads are leveraged. This known issue needs to be
documented until a fix is merged.

Change-Id: Iba8df9385b65f03c0ab9ea07a728e1ccd8e04e86
(cherry picked from commit 0b21419b9daeb27ca9c450051d3adbad46108651)

I don't have a specific problem with the code, per se (although I haven't reviewed it in detail), but I wonder if this is the best way to "fix" what I believe is a problem with the puppet-cinder code used by projects like TripleO. There's nothing fundamentally wrong with using MultiOpt options; it's just that deployment tools need to understand how to configure them.

If people agree there's a cinder problem that this patch will fix, then I'm happy to revisit the patch and resume my review.

And if people feel the real issue lies elsewhere (outside of cinder) then I am willing to work on a puppet-cinder patch.'}, {'account_id': 21129, 'date': '2018-06-13 16:56:46.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5: -Code-Review

(1 comment)

I'm removing my initial objection that the problem that motivated this patch would be better solved elsewhere. Apparently MultiOpt is known to cause headaches for packages that manage config files because a lot of tooling assumes the file follows the INI format, which (rarely) repeat the same option. For example, puppet-cinder uses other Puppet libraries that don't handle MultOpt (or MultiStrOpt) very well.

In other words, adding support for the new ListOpt will make lives easier for a lot of people.

Just one question about whether duplicate entries should be filtered."}, {'account_id': 10379, 'date': '2018-06-13 20:14:41.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 10379, 'date': '2018-06-13 20:16:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

commit_message:
Dell EMC: Added excluded_domain_ips ListOpt to SC driver

Added an excluded_domain_ips option to the Dell EMC SC driver. This
is identical to the excluded_domain_ip option only comma separated
rather than multiple entry. This is concatenated with the
excluded_domain_ip option.

Change-Id: Ib3ab11e776970a850a96fd4e6907b4064396ec3f

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I12f09667569a5cf649346bfa60dccc12de06c136
Story: #2002586
Task: #24319

commit_message:
fix latest release handling in branch validation

Not all repos that create stable branches will have tagged releases,
so only check the latest release when we need to.

Change-Id: Ieb51f8f280a6127ff0adc9432acfe65c809ac764
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Add details and clarify examples on casing

This change adds some more detail to the roles section of the
casing documentation for keystone, as well as clarifying the
examples given for users and projects. Also added project tags
casing.

Neither this, nor the bug, mentions what the actual bad behavior is when the eventlet monkey patch is not turned on. When nova-api runs from the command line (and not under a wsgi server), the basic reason for there being monkey patching is so the built in eventlet web server can handle concurrently accepted connections.

When running under a wsgi server that's the job of the server.

Are there additional concurrency requirements in the api service such that eventlet needs to be on? Is there bad behavior happening that you can point me to so I can understand what is actually being fixed here?

if the only reason eventlet is being added here is because "that's what we do", let's not. But if there are good reasons for it, then please make sure they show up in the commit message.

Thanks.'}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2018-08-16 09:22:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

> Are there additional concurrency requirements in the api service such that eventlet needs to be on? Is there bad behavior happening that you can point me to so I can understand what is actually being fixed here?

It's because when listing instances across multiple cells we're using greenthreads and oslo.db does a time.sleep to allow switching greenthreads:

https://github.com/openstack/oslo.db/blob/9c6695969f6502f52bc86f22af0758715fdc57c0/oslo_db/sqlalchemy/engines.py#L51

Having said that, this change doesn't fix ^ because it doesn't monkey patch the time module. That would have to come in a subsequent change."}, {'account_id': 11564, 'date': '2018-08-16 09:28:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

> It's because when listing instances across multiple cells we're
 > using greenthreads and oslo.db does a time.sleep to allow switching
 > greenthreads:

Ah, okay. That's unfortunate, but I guess the way it goes. If there were a way to make a choice about the type of threading or concurrency that can happen when talking to multiple threads, that might be the most flexible thing to do long term. Intermixing eventlet into the different threading/concurrecy models presented by uwsgi, mod_wsg, gunicorn and all the other various wsgi servers that could potentially be used is likely to be ... interesting.

In any case, a mention in the commit message about the connection to the cells listing would be great, otherwise this seems like this is just "because that's what we do".

Thanks for the quick info.'}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2018-08-16 09:56:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

> In any case, a mention in the commit message about the connection to the cells listing would be great, otherwise this seems like this is just "because that's what we do".

> > Yikun, does this patch fix the concurrency problem you and Kevin
 > were seeing on the multi-cell instance list benchmarks?
 > 
 > My understanding is another patch would be needed on top to monkey
 > patch the time module


Actually this patch, already fix the problem:

eventlet.monkey_patch(os=False, thread=False)

equals to:

eventlet.monkey_patch(builtins=False, socket=True,thread=False,
subprocess=True,MySQLdb=False,psycopg=True,time=True,os=False,select=True)

The "time" flag is True, if we don't set any Flag as True.[1]

The problem is that we didn't enable monkey_patch in uwsgi, so I enable it in [2].


[1] https://github.com/eventlet/eventlet/blob/af407c77f208ceefe5a35e39aed0cf3fdfc07cb9/eventlet/patcher.py#L255
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/592285/6/nova/api/openstack/wsgi_app.py@32'}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2018-08-24 12:42:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

That's not actually what I'm seeing... I'm seeing that the DB calls are not actually done in parallel. The Python gather calls are being gathered in parallel, but the DB queries are still serializing unfortunately. Otherwise, we'd see a reduction in total time spent doing the list operation from ~10s to something less than 10s (since all 10 DB queries would be executed in parallel and the only thing the Python processes would be doing is the heapq merge sort).

 > That's not actually what I'm seeing... I'm seeing that the DB calls
 > are not actually done in parallel. The Python gather calls are
 > being gathered in parallel, but the DB queries are still
 > serializing unfortunately. Otherwise, we'd see a reduction in total
 > time spent doing the list operation from ~10s to something less
 > than 10s (since all 10 DB queries would be executed in parallel and
 > the only thing the Python processes would be doing is the heapq
 > merge sort).

Jay, are you by chance not up to speed on the batching work? The overwhelming amount of time spent here is not doing db queries, but processing the results of the DB queries in python because they're large. I think that's why you don't see the reduction in overall time here. I think their change *is* effective, but not at reducing the time since it's not parallelizeable in the first place. The batching work reduces the amount of waste (and thus time) and this makes us parallelize what we can (AFAIK).

commit_message:
Make monkey patch work in uWSGI mode

There was a eventlet.monkey_patch [1] when we launch a nova
process(like nova-api, nova-compute), but it's invalid under
the uwsgi mode.

But there are concurrency requirements in the api service, such
as, when listing instances cross multiple cells we're using
greenthreads and oslo.db does a time.sleep to allow switching
greenthreads [2].

So, in this patch we add the monkey_patch in the uwsgi
application setup and refactor the monkey patching to use common
code.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/233ea58/nova/cmd/__init__.py#L26
[2] https://github.com/openstack/oslo.db/blob/9c66959/oslo_db/sqlalchemy/engines.py#L51

Closes-bug: #1787331

Change-Id: Ie7bf5d012e2ccbcd63c262ddaf739782afcdaf56

commit_message:
Default embedded instance.flavor.disabled attribute

Before we stored flavors in instance_extra, certain fields, defined
in nova.compute.flavors.system_metadata_flavor_props, were stored
in the instance.system_metadata for the embedded instance.flavor.
The "disabled" field wasn't one of those keys, however, so really
old instances that had their embedded flavor converted to the
serialized instance_extra form won't have the disabled attribute
set and we need to default those here so callers, like the
versioned notfication FlavorPayload, don't explode trying to load
instance.flavor.disabled.

Change-Id: I72f8c11b8b2df1416dec8e2d9250eac0693a30e9
Closes-Bug: #1739325
(cherry picked from commit 8df21c1e5fc46f2774a7653e1c9a4c2ac0b5dbfd)
(cherry picked from commit b2146b02a943c784b6c6fe19ec9e5247bd8e503d)

commit_message:
Revert "Enable configuration of rndc controls"

This has a circular dependency on tripleo-heat-templates that
is blocking promotion.  It was missed by ci because the
designate scenario isn't running on puppet-tripleo.

This reverts commit 158f7543e0203428c8d16554719cbbf64dae1c98.

Closes-Bug: #1788907
Depends-On: Id3dfc9f28e4d204716328eaa9650ab0053d2fdd4
Change-Id: Iedfe995a0960e815cbef749e4fdff81f1bce99fc

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I3d9256eaa20693dc4e2c95da4b5f90e9832c8bf0
Story: #2002586
Task: #24290
